  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the effects of Ceftaroline Fosamil versus Vancomycin
      plus Aztreonam in treatment of patients with complicated bacterial skin and soft tissue
      infections.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A Phase III, Multicentre, Randomised, Double-Blind Comparative Study to Evaluate the Efficacy
      and Safety of Ceftaroline Fosamil (600 mg every 8 hours) Versus Vancomycin Plus Aztreonam in
      the Treatment of Patients with Complicated Bacterial Skin and Soft Tissue Infections With
      Evidence of Systemic Inflammatory Response or Underlying Comorbidities
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
