    <measure>Clinical Response at TOC</measure>
    <time_frame>7 to 20 days after last dose of study drug</time_frame>
    <description>Clinical cure is defined as resolution or improvement of signs and symptoms compared to baseline and no further antimicrobial therapy is necessary. Clinical failure is defined as any of the following: persistence or worsening in signs or symptoms, or requirement for concomitant antibiotic therapy, or requirement of an unplanned surgical intervention &gt;48 hours after the first dose, or death caused by skin infection, or an AE leading to study drug discontinuation with alternative antimicrobial therapy required, or diagnosis of osteomyelitis &gt;=8 days after the first dose.</description>
